gomodel:SYNGO_3008  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099060 replaced by GO:0099634" , "Rationale: GABA B2 subunit detection in Globus pallidus synapses.\n\n11/9/2017 Pim\n- Literal: \" At asymmetric synapses, the majority (85%) of the synapse-associated immunogold particles were located at the edges of the synapse (Fig. 5B), accounting for 34% and 51% for pre- and postsynaptic sites, respectively (Fig. 4B), with only 15% located in the main body (Fig. 5A). However, at symmetric synapses, most (89%) GABAB2 immunogold particles were localized in the main body of the synapses (Fig. 5C-E); 41% associated with the presynaptic membrane and 48% with the postsynaptic membrane (Fig. 4B)\". Experimental description: p.341: Sprague-Dawley rats (Charles River, Margate, Kent; 200 -250 g) used in the present study were maintained on a 12 hour light/dark cycle with free access to food and water. Environmental conditions for housing of the rats, and all procedures performed on them, were in accordance with the Animals (Scientific Procedures) Act 1986 (UK) and in accordance with the European Communities Council Directive (80/609/EEC). All efforts were made to minimize the suffering of the animals. -- Highlighted 11 Aug 2017" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9425-2935" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_3008" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

